

Exceptions

memref.c // program that demonstrates a seg fault due to invalid mem reference
pagefault.c // program that demonstrates a simple page fault



Procs

fork.c // Inline creation of child process and simple test execution

fork2.c // Forks child process, runs separate function for parent and child




Threads

badcnt.c // data race problem

goodcnt.c // corrects data race using semaphores

dlock.c // simple deadlock problem example

dlockfixed.c // fixed deadlock problem by repairing mutex order

mutex.c // another semaphore example (from UW - hallsberg)

nojoin.c // illustrates the unexpected behavior from not joining threads

pc.c // a simple implementation of the producer consumer problem

pcfixed.c // repaired producer consumer problem (incomplete)

semt.c // another semaphore example (from UW - Hallsberg)

Args
	
	args.c // passing structs to multiple threads as arguments

Basic
	
	nonthread.c // trivial increment program without threads

	thread.c // trivial increment program (creates a single thread)

	multi.c // trivial print program (creates multiple threads)


